## üß± Dataset & Data Model

The project uses a clean, relational star-schema model.

Fact table
- Sales_Fact (500‚Äì700 rows)
  - Date ‚Äî Transaction date
  - ProductID ‚Äî FK ‚Üí Products_Dim
  - CustomerID ‚Äî FK ‚Üí Customers_Dim
  - SalesRepID ‚Äî FK ‚Üí SalesRep_Dim
  - Region ‚Äî Sales region
  - UnitsSold ‚Äî Quantity
  - UnitPrice ‚Äî Price per unit
  - Revenue ‚Äî UnitsSold √ó UnitPrice
  - Cost ‚Äî Expense tied to sale
  - Profit ‚Äî Revenue ‚àí Cost

Dimension tables
- Products_Dim
  - ProductName, Category, Subcategory, Brand, LaunchYear
- Customers_Dim
  - Segment (Retail / SMB / Enterprise), AgeGroup, LoyaltyLevel (Bronze ‚Üí Platinum), JoinDate
- SalesRep_Dim
  - Region, ExperienceLevel (Junior / Mid / Senior), JoinYear
- Calendar_Dim
  - Date, Year, MonthNumber, MonthName, Quarter, YearMonth

Notes:
- The model follows a star schema with Sales_Fact at the center and dimension lookups for efficient reporting and time intelligence.

